# ATL Vibes & Views - Environment Configuration
# ==============================================
# These environment variables must be set in Vercel Dashboard:
# Project Settings > Environment Variables

# =====================================
# GeoDirectory REST API Configuration
# =====================================

# Your WordPress site URL (no trailing slash)
# Example: https://yourdomain.com
GEODIR_URL=https://your-wordpress-site.com

# GeoDirectory Consumer Key
# Generated at: WordPress Admin > GeoDirectory > Settings > API > Keys
# Click "Create an API key" with "Read" permissions
GEODIR_KEY=ck_your_consumer_key_here

# GeoDirectory Consumer Secret
# IMPORTANT: Copy this immediately when generated - it won't be shown again!
GEODIR_SECRET=cs_your_consumer_secret_here

# =====================================
# Setup Instructions
# =====================================
#
# 1. Enable REST API in GeoDirectory:
#    - Log into WordPress Admin
#    - Go to GeoDirectory > Settings > API
#    - Check "Enable the REST API"
#    - Save changes
#
# 2. Generate API Keys:
#    - Go to GeoDirectory > Settings > API > Keys
#    - Click "Create an API key"
#    - Description: "ATL Vibes & Views Frontend"
#    - User: Select your admin user
#    - Permissions: "Read" (read-only for public site)
#    - Click "Generate API Key"
#    - Copy BOTH the Consumer Key (ck_...) and Consumer Secret (cs_...)
#
# 3. Add to Vercel:
#    - Go to your Vercel project dashboard
#    - Navigate to Settings > Environment Variables
#    - Add all three variables above
#    - Redeploy your site
#
# 4. Enable in code:
#    - In index.html, set USE_GEODIRECTORY = true
#
# =====================================
# Testing the API
# =====================================
#
# Test directly with curl:
#   curl --user "ck_YOUR_KEY:cs_YOUR_SECRET" \
#     "https://yoursite.com/wp-json/geodir/v2/places"
#
# Test the proxy endpoint after deployment:
#   https://your-vercel-site.vercel.app/api/geodir?endpoint=places&per_page=5

# =====================================
# WordPress SEO Configuration (IMPORTANT)
# =====================================
#
# To prevent duplicate content issues, configure WordPress to NOT be indexed:
#
# Option A: WordPress Settings (Easiest)
#   - Go to Settings > Reading
#   - Check "Discourage search engines from indexing this site"
#
# Option B: Yoast/RankMath SEO Plugin
#   - Go to SEO > Search Appearance
#   - Set GeoDirectory post types (gd_place, gd_event) to "noindex"
#
# Option C: WordPress robots.txt
#   Add to WordPress root:
#     User-agent: *
#     Disallow: /
#     Allow: /wp-json/
#
# Result: WordPress acts as headless CMS (data only)
#         ATL Vibes & Views is the public, SEO-indexed site
